Text.Value: The Radiation and Detection, Indication and Computation System, Radiac Set, is a miniaturized Radiacmeter.
The UDR-14 Radiacmeter detects radiation when Gamma rays interact with Geiger-Müller (GM) tube to produce electrical output pulses

WARNING: Prior to operation of the UDR-14 it is important to check the LCD screen for a replace battery warning. Whenever BAT is displayed, you should replace the batteries as soon as possible since the remaining battery life number is ONLY a very rough approximation.
The set includes a case which is a soft carrying pouch that may be worn on a belt or carried in a pocket.
The UDR-14 Radiacmeter is used for detecting Neutron/Gamma radiation dose or total dose, and Gamma dose rate using the same methodology as a Geiger-Muller counter, also known as a Geiger counter.
